  "texts": [
    "IntroductionThe development of novel pharmaceuticals requires substantial time and financial investments.",
    "Additionally, it is often accompanied by a high risk of failure in the late stages of clinical trials [1][2][3].",
    "To address these challenges, there is an increasing emphasis on repurposing already formulated drugs for novel therapeutic applications.",
    "This approach utilizes comprehensive pharmacological, clinical, and genomic data to identify potential new indications for existing drugs [1,2].",
    "This approach not only significantly accelerates the development process but also reduces the risk of clinical failures, as the safety and tolerability of the substances are already established [1,2].In particular, contemporary computational methodologies, exemplified by systems medicine, have emerged as instrumental in identifying promising candidates, thereby expediting the transition from discovery to clinical application [4]."
  ],
